result.execSummary:
Eric L Jachimiec was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Eric L Jachimiec was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: Called at 10:03 AM. Record was previously called at 8:55 AM but State or Court did not have proper paperwork. Eric Jachimiec appears in person and in custody without counsel. State appears by Charles Simono. Jachimiec states that is the person named in the warrants that Court has copies of, states he was not aware that the warrant was issued for him, makes statement regarding date of warrant and reason for warrant. Court goes thru collaquey for right to attorney, governor's warrant, and habius corpus proceedings. Jachimiec would like to return back to Illinois, reads and signs the Waiver and Consent to Extradition, understands his rights to an attorney, right to habius corpus review and right to governor's warrant. Court finds the defendant freely. voluntarily and intelligently understands his rights. Court signs the waiver and consent to extradition. FOSO to contact Illinois to come and get the defendant.
